  "text": "13 H442 is located in exon 9 at the C-terminus (between membrane-associated helixes 9 and the 3′untranslated region), the area where other missense mutations have been reported (Figure 2c) . The phenotype of a patient with one mutation in the C-terminus region is reportedly mild. [CITATION_1] Considering the mild phenotype of our patient, we suspected that DHCR7 with the H442R mutation exhibited residual enzyme activity. The other mutation, G303R, has been reported in several Japanese cases and is located in exon 8, encoding loop 6-7 within the sterol sensing domain.",
